      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "POWERHOUSE (7) progressive colt who had more to offer with the 60.5kg with a gallant on-pace winner over 1600m at Newcastle in C1 grade. Up sharply in grade with the good weight drop and can surprise again as he stretches out to this trip for the first time. Each way. KENMARE BAY (5) handy staying gelding who will appreciate the sting out of the ground tonight. Charged late with a slashing neck second over 1900m at this track fourth-up. At his peak and shapes as the main danger. PLEASURE ARTIST (2) proven at this course and distance and strips fitter after returning from a let-up with a fading seventh over 1900m at this track. Maps well with Nock's claim, keep safe. GENTILESCHI (6) gets through the going and will appreciate the weight drop in this tougher race. Near her top and will be strong late.",
